<h2>Network Host Analysis</h2>

<h3>Meaning of Network Host</h3>
<p>
A network host is any device connected to a computer network that can send or receive data such as computers, servers, and phones.
</p>

<h3>Analysis</h3>
<p>
Network hosts are used to store, process, and share information across a network system.
</p>

<h3>Functions</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Data storage</li>
    <li>Communication between devices</li>
    <li>Providing network services</li>
</ul>

<h3>Advantages</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Fast communication</li>
    <li>Easy sharing of data</li>
</ul>

<h3>Disadvantages</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Security risks</li>
    <li>Possible system failure</li>
</ul>

